server-valid.description: To configure the SSH server enable or disable.

disable.description: To configure the SSH server disable.
Disable the SSH server. After disable the snetconf server, then the SSH server can be disabled.

enable.description: To configure the SSH server enable.
Enable the SSH server. After enable the SSH server, then the snetconf server can be enabled.

listen-port.description: The listenning port of the SSH server. It can be configured as 22 or any integer between 49152 and 65535. It cannot be changed while SSH server has been enabled.

acl.description: The ACL name which is binded to the SSH server.

ipv4-acl.description: The IPv4 ACL name which is binded to the SSH server.

ipv6-acl.description: The IPv6 ACL name which is binded to the SSH server.

dscp.description: The DSCP value is used in packets of the SSH server. It can be configured any integer between 0 and 63.

authentication.description: Configure the authentication type of SSH server.

user.description:
Configure the authentication type of specified SSH user. SSH user should be configured on ADM_MGR at first.
  If the SSH user only need password authentication, this node may be not configured. 
  If the SSH user need public-key authentication, this node must be configured.

auth-type.description: The authentication type of the SSH server. Include: password authentication, pubblic-key authentication, password and public-key authentication, password or public-key authentication.

key-name.description: The key name used by public-key authentication.

rekey.description: Configure the parameters of regenerate server key.

interval.description:
The interval of regenerate server key. The valid value is any integer between 0 and 720. 
The value of 0 means no regeneration.

diffie-hellman-algorithm.description: Add or remove diffie-hellman algorithms of server
Add or remove diffie-hellman algorithms of client

key-file.description: The key file and path that to be imported.

key-name.description: The public-key name that to be cleared.

key.description: Generate or update public/private key pairs of SSH.

key-type.description: The type of public/private key pairs. Only RSA is supported now.

host-key.description: Generate or update public/private key pairs of SSH.

key-modulus.description: The modulus of the RSA key pair, in bits. default is 1024.
